\title{An R Package to Compute Least Squares Sparse Principal Components}
\Plaintitle{An R package to compute Least Squares Sparse Principal Components}
\Shorttitle{An \proglang{R} package to compute LS-SPCA components}

\Abstract{
This article presents the \pkg{spca} package for computing least-squares sparse principal components (LS-SPCA) in \proglang{R}. LS-SPCA differs from conventional sparse PCA methods because it imposes sparsity on the data-approximation formulation of PCA, rather than on Hotelling's maximum-variance formulation. The package computes uncorrelated, correlated, and projection LS-SPCA components, implements several variable-selection strategies, and provides methods for printing, plotting, summarizing, and comparing \class{spca} objects. This draft contains only the expanded introduction, methodology, and computational sections.
}

\Keywords{SPCA, least squares, sparse PCA, projection, \proglang{R}}
\Plainkeywords{SPCA, least squares, sparse PCA, projection, R}

